# Pointer Cursor on Clickable Elements

Every tappable widget MUST show `SystemMouseCursors.click` on hover for desktop/web.

## Use the `Tappable` Widget

Instead of raw `GestureDetector`, always use the reusable `Tappable` widget (`lib/shared/widgets/tappable.dart`). It wraps `MouseRegion` + `GestureDetector` together:

```dart
import '../../shared/widgets/tappable.dart';

Tappable(
  onTap: () => ...,
  child: MyWidget(),
)
```

`Tappable` automatically shows a pointer cursor when `onTap` or `onLongPress` is set, and falls back to the default cursor when null.

## Exception: Hover-Tracking Widgets

If you need stateful hover tracking (e.g., `onEnter`/`onExit` for hover animations), you still need a raw `MouseRegion` — but MUST include `cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click`:

```dart
MouseRegion(
  cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click,
  onEnter: (_) => setState(() => _hovering = true),
  onExit: (_) => setState(() => _hovering = false),
  child: GestureDetector(onTap: ..., child: ...),
)
```

## Already Handled (don't duplicate)

These core components have pointer cursor built in — no extra wrapping needed:

- `GlassCard` (via `Tappable` internally, when `onTap` is set)
- `GlassButton` (via `MouseRegion` internally, when `onPressed` is set)
- `GlassBottomNav` items (via `Tappable`)
- `_SidebarItem` in `AdaptiveShell` (via `Tappable`)

## Root-Level Overlays

Since detail routes live inside `StatefulShellRoute`, all `showModalBottomSheet` and `showDialog` calls MUST include `useRootNavigator: true` so they render above the persistent navigation bar — not beneath it.

```dart
showModalBottomSheet(
  context: context,
  useRootNavigator: true,
  ...
);

showDialog(
  context: context,
  useRootNavigator: true,
  ...
);
```
